              <span id="reviewTextContainer996895084" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8743394029593471797">I would actually give this book 4.5...I was swept up in this story. Although the plot was very original, the writing style is what embraced me. I was enraptured with the dialogue and setting description. The narration propelled the story with subtlety and attention to details making this story and the characters very believable. The ending felt abrupt and a bit unresolved, but I was satisfied. I did like the idea presented on the last couple of pages, causing me to evaluate how I define the word</span>
  <span id="freeText8743394029593471797" style="display:none">I would actually give this book 4.5...I was swept up in this story. Although the plot was very original, the writing style is what embraced me. I was enraptured with the dialogue and setting description. The narration propelled the story with subtlety and attention to details making this story and the characters very believable. The ending felt abrupt and a bit unresolved, but I was satisfied. I did like the idea presented on the last couple of pages, causing me to evaluate how I define the word family. </span>
