<div id="review_351129453" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/351129453" />
    <a title="Kathryn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1329275-kathryn"><img alt="Kathryn" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/351129453?book_show_action=true">Jun 18, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kathryn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kathryn" href="/user/show/1329275-kathryn">Kathryn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer351129453" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6995433403501251664">Great story, starts out a little slow as you meet the characters and the plot is developed, but then hooks you as you get invested into the characters lives and want to see how they work through their problems on the journey. The journey are ones like: how a person doesn’t choose her family they just are, how to leave the past in behind so you can live for the present and the future, and how the change in feelings can cause a change in relationships.<br/>I really became immersed in the book emotional</span>
  <span id="freeText6995433403501251664" style="display:none">Great story, starts out a little slow as you meet the characters and the plot is developed, but then hooks you as you get invested into the characters lives and want to see how they work through their problems on the journey. The journey are ones like: how a person doesn’t choose her family they just are, how to leave the past in behind so you can live for the present and the future, and how the change in feelings can cause a change in relationships.<br />I really became immersed in the book emotionally, crying over all the hardship that the early saints had to endure, not just he adults, but the children that in a sense lost out on their childhood because the work around the prairies needed doing. I especially had a hard time with the immigrant family, the Chabert family’s story of losing their parents, being split up from their older brother, not speaking the language and having to make all these adjustments at young ages in a foreign land. My heart broke at Maggie perception of her treatment by her adopted mother, Ma Alden. How she let these growing girls run around, didn’t teach them sewing, but had them do the dirty work of collecting eggs, milking cows, chopping wood, while her biological daughters sat inside and were taught how to be ladies and be proper. Ma Alden’s brother’s boy, Jed would tease and hurt the two girls sometimes even cutting them with knifes with no repercussions. Maggie was a free spirit and liked to fish and swim in the river with her two friends Henry and Mariah, but when Mariah moved back to SL, she was left behind with just Henry and the atmosphere changed between them. Then the soldiers came to investigate the killings of some saints by “the Indians”, but really it was white people dressed up and the government gets involved and the saints resist their involvement creating a Calvery up in the mountains.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="6995433403501251664" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


